179  protected static BigInteger convertLongToUlong(long longVal) {
180  byte[] asBytes = new byte[8];
181  asBytes[7] = (byte) (longVal & 0xff);
182  asBytes[6] = (byte) (longVal >>> 8);
183  asBytes[5] = (byte) (longVal >>> 16);
184  asBytes[4] = (byte) (longVal >>> 24);
185  asBytes[3] = (byte) (longVal >>> 32);
186  asBytes[2] = (byte) (longVal >>> 40);
187  asBytes[1] = (byte) (longVal >>> 48);
188  asBytes[0] = (byte) (longVal >>> 56);
189 
190  return new BigInteger(1, asBytes);

596  public boolean absolute(int row) throws SQLException {
597  synchronized (checkClosed().getConnectionMutex()) {
598 
599  boolean b;
600 
601  if (this.rowData.size() == 0) {
602  b = false;
603  } else {
604  if (this.onInsertRow) {
605  this.onInsertRow = false;
606  }
607 
608  if (this.doingUpdates) {
609  this.doingUpdates = false;
610  }
611 
612  if (this.thisRow != null) {
613  this.thisRow.closeOpenStreams();
614  }
615 
616  if (row == 0) {
617  beforeFirst();
618  b = false;
619  } else if (row == 1) {
620  b = first();
621  } else if (row == -1) {
622  b = last();
623  } else if (row > this.rowData.size()) {
624  afterLast();
625  b = false;
626  } else {
627  if (row < 0) {
628  // adjust to reflect after end of result set
629  int newRowPosition = this.rowData.size() + row + 1;
630 
631  if (newRowPosition <= 0) {
632  beforeFirst();
633  b = false;
634  } else {
635  b = absolute(newRowPosition);
636  }
637  } else {
638  row--; // adjust for index difference
639  this.rowData.setCurrentRow(row);
640  this.thisRow = this.rowData.getAt(row);
641  b = true;
642  }
643  }
644  }
645 
646  setRowPositionValidity();
647 
648  return b;
649  }
650  }

733  public void buildIndexMapping() throws SQLException {
734  int numFields = this.fields.length;
735  this.columnLabelToIndex = new TreeMap<String, Integer>(String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER);
736  this.fullColumnNameToIndex = new TreeMap<String, Integer>(String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER);
737  this.columnNameToIndex = new TreeMap<String, Integer>(String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER);
738 
739  // We do this in reverse order, so that the 'first' column
740  // with a given name ends up as the final mapping in the
741  // hashtable...
742  //
743  // Quoting the JDBC Spec:
744  //
745  // "Column names used as input to getter
746  // methods are case insensitive. When a getter method is called with a
747  // column
748  // name and several columns have the same name, the value of the first
749  // matching column will be returned. "
750  //
751  for (int i = numFields - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
752  Integer index = Integer.valueOf(i);
753  String columnName = this.fields[i].getOriginalName();
754  String columnLabel = this.fields[i].getName();
755  String fullColumnName = this.fields[i].getFullName();
756 
757  if (columnLabel != null) {
758  this.columnLabelToIndex.put(columnLabel, index);
759  }
760 
761  if (fullColumnName != null) {
762  this.fullColumnNameToIndex.put(fullColumnName, index);
763  }
764 
765  if (columnName != null) {
766  this.columnNameToIndex.put(columnName, index);
767  }
768  }
769 
770  // set the flag to prevent rebuilding...
771  this.hasBuiltIndexMapping = true;
772  }

1651  public boolean getBoolean(int columnIndex) throws SQLException {
1652 
1653  checkColumnBounds(columnIndex);
1654 
1655  //
1656  // MySQL 5.0 and newer have an actual BIT type,
1657  // so we need to check for that here...
1658  //
1659

1661 
1662  Field field = this.fields[columnIndexMinusOne];
1663 
1664  if (field.getMysqlType() == MysqlDefs.FIELD_TYPE_BIT) {
1665  return byteArrayToBoolean(columnIndexMinusOne);
1666  }
1667 
1668  this.wasNullFlag = false;
1669 
1670  int sqlType = field.getSQLType();
1671 
1672  switch (sqlType) {
1673  case Types.BOOLEAN:
1674  if (field.getMysqlType() == -1) { // from dbmd

1677  return getBooleanFromString(stringVal);

1681 
1682  return (boolVal == -1 || boolVal > 0);
1683  case Types.BIT:
1684  case Types.TINYINT:
1685  case Types.SMALLINT:
1686  case Types.INTEGER:
1687  case Types.BIGINT:
1688  case Types.DECIMAL:
1689  case Types.NUMERIC:
1690  case Types.REAL:
1691  case Types.FLOAT:
1692  case Types.DOUBLE:
1693  boolVal = getLong(columnIndex, false);
1694 
1695  return (boolVal == -1 || boolVal > 0);
1696  default:
1697  if (this.connection.getPedantic()) {
1698  // Table B-6 from JDBC spec
1699  switch (sqlType) {
1700  case Types.BINARY:
1701  case Types.VARBINARY:
1702  case Types.LONGVARBINARY:
1703  case Types.DATE:
1704  case Types.TIME:
1705  case Types.TIMESTAMP:
1706  case Types.CLOB:
1707  case Types.BLOB:
1708  case Types.ARRAY:
1709  case Types.REF:
1710  case Types.DATALINK:
1711  case Types.STRUCT:
1712  case Types.JAVA_OBJECT:
1713  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Required type conversion not allowed",
1714  SQLError.SQL_STATE_INVALID_CHARACTER_VALUE_FOR_CAST, getExceptionInterceptor());
1715  }
1716  }

1718  if (sqlType == Types.BINARY ||
1719  sqlType == Types.VARBINARY ||
1720  sqlType == Types.LONGVARBINARY ||
1721  sqlType == Types.BLOB) {
1722  return byteArrayToBoolean(columnIndexMinusOne);

7843  private void throwRangeException(String valueAsString, int columnIndex,
7844  int jdbcType) throws SQLException {
7845  String datatype = null;
7846 
7847  switch (jdbcType) {
7848  case Types.TINYINT:
7849  datatype = "TINYINT";
7850  break;
7851  case Types.SMALLINT:
7852  datatype = "SMALLINT";
7853  break;
7854  case Types.INTEGER:
7855  datatype = "INTEGER";
7856  break;
7857  case Types.BIGINT:
7858  datatype = "BIGINT";
7859  break;
7860  case Types.REAL:
7861  datatype = "REAL";
7862  break;
7863  case Types.FLOAT:
7864  datatype = "FLOAT";
7865  break;
7866  case Types.DOUBLE:
7867  datatype = "DOUBLE";
7868  break;
7869  case Types.DECIMAL:
7870  datatype = "DECIMAL";
7871  break;
7872  default:
7873  datatype = " (JDBC type '" + jdbcType + "')";
7874  }
7875 
7876  throw SQLError.createSQLException("'" + valueAsString + "' in column '"
7877  + columnIndex + "' is outside valid range for the datatype "
7878  + datatype + ".", SQLError.SQL_STATE_NUMERIC_VALUE_OUT_OF_RANGE, getExceptionInterceptor());
7879  }
